    "post_content": "<h3><b>1. Job Description</b></h3>\r\n<em><b>Planning</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Verify recruitment needs/requests from Departments;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Make a recruitment plan: channel, cost, approaching,...</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Executing</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Search and look for suitable candidates;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Screen CVs and setup interviews;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Inform feedback and result of the interview to candidates;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Negotiate about working conditions and benefits;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Make recruitment reports by statistics of candidate data, recruitment costs and other necessary information.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Onboarding</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implement and coordinate procedures for new employees (seats, machines, contracts, employee records, ...);</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Integration training for new employees.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Following the probation</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coordinate with Department Manager to evaluate the probation and sign contract/terminate the probation with the respective new employees;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Employer branding</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Comply with the company's requirements and policies on the recruitment process;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Respond to candidates' inquiries in a polite, appropriate and prompt manner;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Work with training institutions, universities to source and build recruitment brand;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Make a survey of candidate experience, statistics and timely adjustment suggestions;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Connect with employees, learn about employees' thoughts and aspirations in order to advise the Board of Directors on timely solutions in labor relations.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Others</b></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Participate in assigned training activities;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Perform other tasks as requested by supervisors.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>2. Compensation &amp; Benefits</b><b>\r\n</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Saturday &amp; Sunday OFF,  Overtime pay is 150%, 200%, 300% as per labor law;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Salary review 2 times/ year, based on work performance and company’s performance;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Performance bonus, 13th- month salary, public holidays bonus (2/9, 30/4, 1/5, 1/1); bonus for Excellent Employee and Excellent Team;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Social insurance, health insurance, unemployment insurance and Bao Viet care insurance;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">01 hour paid leave per day for women having children under 12 months</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Minimum 14 paid leaves per annum for all employees after probation;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nice &amp; modern working space with young, dynamic &amp; friendly colleagues and free coffee, tea, drinks;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yearly company trip and year-end party, quarterly team building and weekly eating together; English - Japanese Club, Sports Clubs;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Men’s Day, Women’s Day, Children’s Day, Mid-Autumn Festival and other benefits under the provisions of the company;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Flat, open and sharing culture with friendly management team; outsourcing company with product mindset;</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Training courses and working opportunities with technical gurus who built and operated world-class applications with millions of users. This might be a good chance for graduated students to learn cutting-edge technologies and how to build scalable system from scratch;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>3. Requirements</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b><i>At least 6 months of experience in recruiting IT positions in outsourcing companies</i></b></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bachelor of HR, economics, business administration or related fields</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have knowledge of IT services and the labor market</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Agile, proactive in work, able to work independently as well as in a good team</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Excellent skill of persuasion, negotiation and communication</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Positive &amp; results-oriented mindset with logical thinking</span></li>\r\n \t<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fast learner &amp; change adapter.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"title\"><strong>4. How to apply</strong></h3>\r\n<div class=\"contact\">Feel free to apply even if you feel like you don’t fully match the description above. Letters of interest and CVs in English should sent electronically to us (<span style=\"color: #00aae7;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #00aae7;\" href=\"mailto:hr@sotatek.com\">hr@sotatek.com</a></strong></span>) with subject \"<strong>Application for IT Recruiter</strong>\"\r\nShould you have any queries, please feel free to contact us:\r\nEmail:<strong> <span style=\"color: #00aae7;\"><a style=\"color: #00aae7;\" href=\"mailto:hr@sotatek.com\">hr@sotatek.com</a></span></strong>\r\nFB Fanpage: <span style=\"color: #00aae7;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #00aae7;\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/SotaTek-Recruitment-103449144861080\">SotaTek Recruitment</a></strong></span>\r\nTel: 024-6672-2259</div>",
